# STANDALONE feedback-triage surface (issue #59): the second build entry ships as
# the static file `dist/feedback-admin.html`. Cloudflare Pages' built-in clean-URL
# handling ALREADY serves it at the extensionless path `/feedback-admin` (and
# 308-redirects the explicit `/feedback-admin.html` → `/feedback-admin`), exactly
# like it serves `index.html` at `/`. So NO custom rule is needed here.
#
# ⚠️ Do NOT add `/feedback-admin  /feedback-admin.html  200`. It caused an infinite
# 308 loop (issue #59, PR #67 fix): the rewrite sends `/feedback-admin` →
# `/feedback-admin.html`, which Pages' clean-URL layer 308s straight back to
# `/feedback-admin`, re-matching the rewrite forever (observed `Location:
# /feedback-admin`, ERR_TOO_MANY_REDIRECTS). Real static files (including
# `feedback-admin.html` at its clean path, /assets/*, /data/*, /sw.js) are served
# by Pages BEFORE any `_redirects` rule, so the surface is reachable by direct URL
# with no rule at all.

# SPA fallback: serve index.html for any path that isn't a real static file.
